&lt;p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'>            &lt;/p>
&lt;p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'>            &lt;span
style='font-size:12.0pt'>Sin involves two issues that correspond to the two
sides of a sin situation. There is the doing of a moral wrong and the reacting
to a moral wrong. Because sin takes place between people, there is the person
who does evil and the one who suffers evil. In resolving that circumstance,
repentance happens on one side and forgiveness happens on the other.&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>TWO SYSTEMS FOR RIGHTEOUSNESS</title><link>https://christir.org/essays/topics/christian-doctrine/salvation-soteriology/two-systems-for-righteousness/</link><pubDate>Thu, 02 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/essays/topics/christian-doctrine/salvation-soteriology/two-systems-for-righteousness/</guid><description>&lt;style>
